# 6. Lessons Learned

- FTP anonymous access can leak sensitive backups  
- password-protected archives can be cracked with John  
- weak hashing (MD5) is easily broken  
- SQL injection can lead to full system compromise  
- sqlmap can automate exploitation and provide shell access  
- always check sudo permissions for privilege escalation  
- vi can be abused to spawn root shell  

